<h1>David Eppstein - Publications</h1>
<hr><p>
<h2>
</h2>
<ul>
<li><b>Optimally fast incremental Manhattan plane embedding and planar
tight span construction</b>.<br>
D. Eppstein.<br>
<a href="//arxiv.org/abs/0909.1866">arXiv:0909.1866</a>.<br>
<a href="//doi.org/10.20382/jocg.v2i1a8"><i>J. Computational Geometry</i> 2 (1): 144&ndash;182, 2011</a>.
<p>
Shows that, when the tight span of a finite metric space is homeomorphic
to a subset of the plane, it has the geometry of
a <a href="p-manhattan">Manhattan orbifold</a> and can be constructed in
time linear in the size of the input distance matrix. As a consequence,
it can be tested in the same time whether a metric space is isometric to
a subset of the L<sub>1</sub> plane.
<p>
</ul>

